cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.SY

This paper focuses on the use of deep learning and edge computing for caching entertainment content in self-driving cars. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as it deals with the communication and networking aspects of the proposed solution. The use of deep learning also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category. The paper also uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for predicting the age and gender of passengers, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The caching aspect of the solution suggests that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques to minimize content downloading delay suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category.
